Are Bound To Repeat It.


03 Jul 2018 07:48






Well, here we are. Conwell's submission to the 4000 Contest. While not as grand as some of the other entries, I'd like to think its a decent article on its own, and under 2000 words to boot. Apologies to Mr. Fred Rogers.

Special thanks to those who helped get it all ship shape:

+block

–block


About Deer College
SCP-3108
The Great Hippo's Proposal (feat. PeppersGhost)
Comedown Machine
Sooperrandomname
SCP-3817
SCP-516
You Can Leave Your Friends Behind
SCP-3305
I Hope I Get Old Before I Die
SCP-2696
SCP-2317-J
SCP-1994
Hypervelocity
SCP-2630
SCP-3353
SCP-3703
SCP-3760
SCP-3435
Every Damn Time





For those interested in spoilers:

+block

–block


Year after year, the muse Clio has attempted to inspire a history lesson on 15/11, only to have the attempt blocked by her sister muse Melpomene. There is a certain tragedy in failing to fulfil your main purpose in your pantheon, afterall. This has continued through out history, in different eras. Melpomene only finally lost interest in tormenting her sister when Clio finally managed to have the inspired lecture completed with the help of the Foundation.

This does beg the question, however, that if the muses of Greco-Roman myth are hanging around, what other members of the Pantheon also exist.




Thanks for the read.

JC







